                "html": "<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">Red. Turning your otter, like it solves the problem that Blue Red has,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">which is that Blue Red is like, hey, can you just give me a sec? I'm gonna play my two mana one ones and my three mana two twos. And Patchwork Banner says, hey, I'll trigger those,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">plus I will give a permanent buff to those cards. And all of a sudden, your otter ball antics is making a two mana two two with Prowess and flashes back.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">A three three with Prowess. And that is a lot better. Plus, Patchwork Banner triggers all of that non-creature stuff.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">So I've drafted Blue Red a few times and I've found it to be like, and once again, this is not a good deck, but I think-You were really selling folks here.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">I just wanna put the caveat on, it's just like, you're gonna, I think, especially if you're drafting, maybe not in the best of one ladder,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">but if you're drafting in any kind of competitive pods, you're gonna have to draft Blue Red at some point. Yes. And you're gonna wanna know how to draft it.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">And I think Patchwork Banner's really important in those decks. And it feels to me like, you remember drafting Blue Red in OTJ? And it was just like, no one wanted to touch it.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">And so the pods where three or four of the Blue Red rares were opened, you just got them. Like you just get past, I got a pack one pick three Ral the other day,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">and then I got past Alania. And it was just like, okay, no one wants to draft Blue Red, I'll draft Blue Red. But then when the deck is so open,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">you do need to know what the pieces are that really like, oh, what do I need to do? And so the two cards that I've been impressed by, Patchwork Banner for sure is like,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">you gotta have that in your Blue Red decks 'cause it makes your creatures big, right? Again, makes your Kindle Spark duos being two fours.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">All of a sudden you're like, oh, that's not a bad card at all. And leveraging Wildfire Howl has been very good here. The one red red deal two to all creatures and you can gift a card to deal one damage to something and then two to all creatures.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">'Cause that shores up your matchup against rabbits, which is the archetype that that struggles with the most. Yes, exactly.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">And a lot of the times those, because you have a lot of card selection, card advantage, when it's bad, you can usually chuck it in some way. And so I just found that I really wanna make sure I have access to a copy of that in Blue Red.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">You're selling me on Patchwork Banner. That makes sense because when you get that deck also, you're likely to get all the otters because nobody else wants them anyway.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">So you're going to end up in that type of streamlined deck where Patchwork Banner's great. Yeah, correct, yeah. Yeah, it makes sense.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">I mean, it's unlike, again, Patchwork Banner is a card that is gonna be contested. But so if you find yourself in Blue Red and you're opening up a pack that has Banner versus Red removal spell,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">I think you'd just be inclined to be like, \"Oh, I should take take out the trash.\" And I would say, \"No,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">you really wanna make sure \"you have Banner in that deck.\" Yeah, I buy it. I was trying to have another category here of once I have two of these,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">my pick order changes 'cause I was kind of inspired by having two jolly durbels in a draft earlier this week. And that's the one in a white two, three,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">that whenever you gift something, you draw a card. And I've been impressed by this on the other side of the battlefield as well.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">And I just couldn't find other cards that fit this category of like, \"When I have two, I'm gonna start to mess around.\" That I haven't already sort of listed in other categories here in this episode.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">I would say Eddy Merc Crab. Once I get the second Eddy Merc Crab, I'm pretty interested in spells. Yes, I totally agree.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">But that feels more like sign posty slash, that's just like, that's good. That's like clearly what that-That's just good drafting.</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">That's just good drafting, I would say. And that's clearly like what that card and deck is doing. But I guess it's, you could be blue red,</p> \n<p data-tool=\"mdnice编辑器\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.8em; letter-spacing: 0em; text-align: left; text-indent: 0em; margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; padding-top: 8px; padding-bottom: 8px; padding-left: 0px; padding-right: 0px;\">but you'd probably just prefer to be blue black with that. I would prefer to be blue black with that, yeah.</p>",
